response.original_title: The Nature of Modernism: E. Stewart Williams, Architect
response.overview: E. Stewart Williams was a prolific modernist architect based in Palm Springs, California. Follow Williams' history and professional career, from the early days designing a home for Frank Sinatra, to the later years, producing iconic public buildings. With access to never-before-seen material, this compelling documentary provides an intimate portrait of a desert modernist master.
response.title: The Nature of Modernism: E. Stewart Williams, Architect
